          "pot"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You lost your pack about a year ago, casualties of the ongoing war between the Sabbat and Camarilla. They were a good, solid pack and you've been hesitant to join a new one, even though you get some serious side-eye from your fellow Sabbat as a result. But it turned out to be for the best when you were sent to Los Angeles, the diocese of Archbishop Guzman. Guzman needs eyes in the Camarilla, and picked you for the job. Eventually, says Guzman, the Sabbat will launch a Crusade against the Camarilla of Los Angeles. And whe that happens, he wants someone able to wreck things from the inside while the rest of the Sword of Caine attacks from without. It's dangerous, since you will be without the protections of the Vaulderie (Guzman says he can Vaulderie with you once a year or so, but doesn't want to risk more than that), but he's confident you're the best person for the job. You found a Gangrel on his way into the city, and nabbed him before he could make his way into Camarilla territory. A little Vicissitude, and you look exactly like him, your beast marks covering up your Vicissitude scars. Even better, you've got furry hands - the better to hide your Black Hand brand."
        ],
